<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE - Flywheel
        (Manual Transmission)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Flywheel (Manual Transmission)</title>
        <figure id="f2651305" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0702.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 457. Flywheel guides</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M10 x 77 flywheel mounting bolts at approximately the 3 o'clock and 9 o'clock
                positions. Install two guide pins (make locally).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove remaining eight flywheel mounting bolts and reinforcement ring. Discard all ten
                mounting bolts as they are not reusable.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651306" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 458. Flywheel guide pins</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide flywheel out of housing and off guide pins. With flywheel removed, guide pins can be
                removed from secondary flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
